{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775858795521,"sessionID":"ses_286938d3effeSPFC7LqkvWW4EL","part":{"id":"prt_d796ec3eb001ZOLCRjB0pYL0We","messageID":"msg_d796ce3800014YQPMXrM1P0rM2","sessionID":"ses_286938d3effeSPFC7LqkvWW4EL","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-366b145174d942fcb8dcc35486fc7a3a","state":{"status":"error","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md","content":"# Delta Spec: AR-014 â€” Valkey å­˜å‚¨å®žçŽ°\n\n## Module\n`pkg/store`\n\n## Language\nGo\n\n## Size\nS\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Valkey client initialization\nThe system SHALL create a Valkey client using `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` when `STORE_TYPE=valkey`.\n\n### Scenario: Valkey client created with required options\n- **GIVEN** environment variable `STORE_TYPE=valkey` (case-insensitive)\n- **AND** `VALKEY_ADDR` is set to a comma-separated address list\n- **AND** `VALKEY_PASSWORD` is set (or `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false`)\n- **WHEN** `initStore()` executes\n- **THEN** a `valkeyStore` struct is created with `valkey.Client` initialized using `ClientOption.InitAddress` from split addresses\n\n### Scenario: Valkey password optional when disabled\n- **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE=valkey`\n- **AND** `VALKEY_ADDR` is set\n- **AND** `VALKEY_PASSWORD` is empty\n- **AND** `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false`\n- **WHEN** `initStore()` executes\n- **THEN** initialization succeeds without password\n\n### Scenario: Valkey initialization fails without address\n- **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE=valkey`\n- **AND** `VALKEY_ADDR` is not set\n- **WHEN** `initStore()` executes\n- **THEN** initialization fails with error indicating `VALKEY_ADDR` is required\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Valkey optional client flags\nThe system SHALL support optional `DisableCache` and `ForceSingleClient` flags via environment variables.\n\n### Scenario: DisableCache enabled\n- **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE=valkey`\n- **AND** `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE=true`\n- **WHEN** Valkey client options are built\n- **THEN** `ClientOption.DisableCache` is set to `true`\n\n### Scenario: ForceSingleClient enabled\n- **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE=valkey`\n- **AND** `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE=true`\n- **WHEN** Valkey client options are built\n- **THEN** `ClientOption.ForceSingleClient` is set to `true`\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Valkey Ping implementation\nThe system SHALL implement `Ping` using Valkey's command builder API.\n\n### Scenario: Ping returns PONG\n- **GIVEN** a connected Valkey client\n- **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called\n- **THEN** the command `B().Ping().Build()` is executed\n- **AND** the response string equals `\"PONG\"`\n\n### Scenario: Ping returns error on failure\n- **GIVEN** a disconnected or unhealthy Valkey server\n- **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called\n- **THEN** an error is returned\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Valkey GetSandboxBySessionID implementation\nThe system SHALL retrieve sandbox JSON by session ID and return `ErrNotFound` for missing keys.\n\n### Scenario: Get existing session\n- **GIVEN** a session key `session:{sessionID}` exists with valid JSON\n- **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID)` is called\n- **THEN** command `B().Get().Key(\"session:{sessionID}\").Build()` is executed\n- **AND** the response is unmarshaled to `*types.SandboxInfo`\n- **AND** the sandbox is returned with no error\n\n### Scenario: Get missing session returns ErrNotFound\n- **GIVEN** no key `session:{sessionID}` exists\n- **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID)` is called\n- **THEN** the Valkey response has `IsValkeyNil()` true\n- **AND** error returned is `ErrNotFound`\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Valkey StoreSandbox implementation\nThe system SHALL atomically store session JSON and update both sorted set indexes.\n\n### Scenario: Store new sandbox successfully\n- **GIVEN** a valid `*types.SandboxInfo` with non-zero `ExpiresAt`\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n- **THEN** commands are executed via `DoMulti`:\n  - `SETNX` on key `session:{sessionID}` with JSON value\n  - `ZADD` on `session:expiry` with score `ExpiresAt.Unix()` and member `sessionID`\n  - `ZADD` on `session:last_activity` with score `time.Now().Unix()` and member `sessionID`\n- **AND** no error is returned\n\n### Scenario: Store rejects nil sandbox\n- **GIVEN** `sandbox` parameter is nil\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, nil)` is called\n- **THEN** error is returned indicating sandbox cannot be nil\n\n### Scenario: Store rejects zero ExpiresAt\n- **GIVEN** `sandbox.ExpiresAt` is zero time\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n- **THEN** error is returned indicating ExpiresAt must be set\n\n### Scenario: Store fails on SETNX conflict\n- **GIVEN** key `session:{sessionID}` already exists\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n- **THEN** `SETNX` returns false\n- **AND** error is returned indicating session already exists\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Valkey UpdateSandbox implementation\nThe system SHALL update only the session JSON value using SET with XX flag, without modifying indexes.\n\n### Scenario: Update existing sandbox\n- **GIVEN** key `session:{sessionID}` exists\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n- **THEN** command `SET key value XX` is executed\n- **AND** response `ToString()` equals `\"OK\"`\n- **AND** no error is returned\n\n### Scenario: Update non-existent sandbox fails\n- **GIVEN** key `session:{sessionID}` does not exist\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n- **THEN** command `SET key value XX` is executed\n- **AND** response `ToString()` does not equal `\"OK\"`\n- **AND** error is returned indicating key does not exist\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Valkey DeleteSandboxBySessionID implementation\nThe system SHALL atomically delete session key and remove from both sorted sets.\n\n### Scenario: Delete existing session\n- **GIVEN** session `sessionID` exists in key and both ZSETs\n- **WHEN** `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID)` is called\n- **THEN** commands are executed via `DoMulti`:\n  - `DEL` on key `session:{sessionID}`\n  - `ZREM` on `session:expiry` with member `sessionID`\n  - `ZREM` on `session:last_activity` with member `sessionID`\n- **AND** no error is returned\n\n### Scenario: Delete non-existent session succeeds\n- **GIVEN** session `sessionID` does not exist\n- **WHEN** `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID)` is called\n- **THEN** operation completes without error\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Valkey ListExpiredSandboxes implementation\nThe system SHALL query expiry sorted set and load corresponding sandbox documents.\n\n### Scenario: List expired sessions\n- **GIVEN** `session:expiry` ZSET contains members with scores â‰¤ `before.Unix()`\n- **WHEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` is called with `limit > 0`\n- **THEN** command `ZRANGEBYSCORE` is executed with:\n  - key `session:expiry`\n  - min `-inf`\n  - max `fmt.Sprintf(\"%d\", before.Unix())`\n  - `Limit(0, limit)`\n- **AND** for each session ID returned, corresponding JSON is loaded\n- **AND** slice of `*types.SandboxInfo` is returned\n\n### Scenario: List expired with zero limit returns nil\n- **GIVEN** `limit <= 0`\n- **WHEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` is called\n- **THEN** `nil, nil` is returned without backend queries\n\n### Scenario: List expired tolerates orphan ZSET members\n- **GIVEN** session ID exists in `session:expiry` but `session:{id}` key is missing\n- **WHEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes` loads sandboxes\n- **THEN** the orphan session is skipped (not included in result)\n- **AND** no error is returned\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Valkey ListInactiveSandboxes implementation\nThe system SHALL query last-activity sorted set and load corresponding sandbox documents.\n\n### Scenario: List inactive sessions\n- **GIVEN** `session:last_activity` ZSET contains members with scores â‰¤ `before.Unix()`\n- **WHEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` is called with `limit > 0`\n- **THEN** command `ZRANGEBYSCORE` is executed on `session:last_activity`\n- **AND** for each session ID returned, corresponding JSON is loaded\n- **AND** slice of `*types.SandboxInfo` is returned\n\n### Scenario: List inactive with zero limit returns nil\n- **GIVEN** `limit <= 0`\n- **WHEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` is called\n- **THEN** `nil, nil` is returned without backend queries\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Valkey UpdateSessionLastActivity implementation\nThe system SHALL update last-activity ZSET score after verifying session exists.\n\n### Scenario: Update activity for existing session\n- **GIVEN** key `session:{sessionID}` exists\n- **AND** `at` parameter is a valid time\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, sessionID, at)` is called\n- **THEN** key existence is checked via `EXISTS` command\n- **AND** command `ZADD session:last_activity {at.Unix()} {sessionID}` is executed\n- **AND** no error is returned\n\n### Scenario: Update activity uses current time when at is zero\n- **GIVEN** key `session:{sessionID}` exists\n- **AND** `at` parameter is zero time\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, sessionID, at)` is called\n- **THEN** `time.Now()` is used for the score\n- **AND** ZADD command is executed with current Unix timestamp\n\n### Scenario: Update activity for non-existent session fails\n- **GIVEN** key `session:{sessionID}` does not exist\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, sessionID, at)` is called\n- **THEN** `EXISTS` returns 0\n- **AND** `ErrNotFound` is returned\n\n### Scenario: Update activity rejects empty session ID\n- **GIVEN** `sessionID` parameter is empty string\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"\", at)` is called\n- **THEN** error is returned indicating session ID cannot be empty\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Valkey Close implementation\nThe system SHALL close the Valkey client connection.\n\n### Scenario: Close client successfully\n- **GIVEN** a connected Valkey client\n- **WHEN** `Close()` is called\n- **THEN** `valkey.Client.Close()` is invoked\n- **AND** `nil` is returned\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: MGET optimization for loading sandboxes\nThe system SHALL use a single MGET command when loading multiple sandbox documents by session IDs.\n\n### Scenario: Load multiple sandboxes with MGET\n- **GIVEN** a list of session IDs from ZRANGEBYSCORE\n- **WHEN** `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs` is called\n- **THEN** all `session:{id}` keys are collected\n- **AND** a single `MGET` command is built with all keys\n- **AND** results are processed to skip empty/missing values\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Provider type constants\nThe system SHALL define provider type constants for type identification.\n\n### Scenario: Valkey store type constant\n- **GIVEN** the `singleton.go` file\n- **WHEN** constants are defined\n- **THEN** `valkeyStoreType string = \"valkey\"` exists\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: ZSET score semantics\nThe system SHALL use Unix timestamp integers as ZSET scores for both expiry and last-activity indexes.\n\n### Scenario: Expiry score is Unix timestamp\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox with `ExpiresAt` time\n- **WHEN** stored to ZSET `session:expiry`\n- **THEN** score is `float64(sandbox.ExpiresAt.Unix())`\n\n### Scenario: Last activity score is Unix timestamp\n- **GIVEN** a timestamp `at` (or `time.Now()` if zero)\n- **WHEN** stored to ZSET `session:last_activity`\n- **THEN** score is `float64(at.Unix())`"},"error":"You must read file /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md before overwriting it. Use the Read tool first","time":{"start":1775858795515,"end":1775858795519}}}}
