{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775858799623,"sessionID":"ses_286938d3effeSPFC7LqkvWW4EL","part":{"id":"prt_d796ed3d0001fMeRNzrzvzbl1f","messageID":"msg_d796ec459001jayrUrF0bkeojD","sessionID":"ses_286938d3effeSPFC7LqkvWW4EL","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-381e1b4186d943a28ef7ee9f531f6371","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-013: Redis Storage Implementation\n2: \n3: Module: `pkg/store`\n4: Language: Go\n5: Size: M\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## Overview\n10: \n11: Implement Redis-backed session storage for persisting sandbox metadata keyed by session ID, with sorted set indexes for expiry and last-activity tracking.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Requirements\n16: \n17: ### REQ-001: Store Interface\n18: \n19: **GIVEN** the system needs to persist sandbox metadata  \n20: **WHEN** managing session storage  \n21: **THEN** Store interface shall be properly defined with all required methods\n22: \n23: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n24: \n25: ```go\n26: // Scenario 1: Store interface definition\n27: GIVEN pkg/store/store.go\n28: WHEN reading the Store interface\n29: THEN it SHALL define Ping(ctx context.Context) error\n30: AND it SHALL define GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n31: AND it SHALL define StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n32: AND it SHALL define UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n33: AND it SHALL define DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n34: AND it SHALL define ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n35: AND it SHALL define ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n36: AND it SHALL define UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error\n37: AND it SHALL define Close() error\n38: \n39: // Scenario 2: ErrNotFound exported\n40: GIVEN pkg/store/store.go\n41: WHEN reading the error variable\n42: THEN ErrNotFound SHALL be defined as errors.New(\"store: not found\")\n43: ```\n44: \n45: ---\n46: \n47: ### REQ-002: Redis Store Type Constants\n48: \n49: **GIVEN** multiple backend providers need identification  \n50: **WHEN** selecting storage backend  \n51: **THEN** provider type constants shall be defined\n52: \n53: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n54: \n55: ```go\n56: // Scenario 1: Redis store type constant\n57: GIVEN pkg/store/singleton.go\n58: WHEN reading constants\n59: THEN redisStoreType SHALL be \"redis\"\n60: \n61: // Scenario 2: Valkey store type constant\n62: GIVEN pkg/store/singleton.go\n63: WHEN reading constants\n64: THEN valkeyStoreType SHALL be \"valkey\"\n65: ```\n66: \n67: ---\n68: \n69: ### REQ-003: Singleton Access\n70: \n71: **GIVEN** single storage instance needed across application  \n72: **WHEN** accessing storage  \n73: **THEN** singleton pattern shall be implemented\n74: \n75: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n76: \n77: ```go\n78: // Scenario 1: Storage function exists\n79: GIVEN pkg/store/singleton.go\n80: WHEN reading the exported function\n81: THEN Storage() SHALL return Store interface\n82: \n83: // Scenario 2: sync.Once used\n84: GIVEN pkg/store/singleton.go\n85: WHEN reading initialization logic\n86: THEN initStoreOnce SHALL be of type *sync.Once\n87: AND provider SHALL be of type Store\n88: \n89: // Scenario 3: Single initialization\n90: GIVEN multiple goroutines calling Storage()\n91: WHEN they execute concurrently\n92: THEN initStore SHALL execute exactly once via initStoreOnce.Do()\n93: \n94: // Scenario 4: Init failure is fatal\n95: GIVEN initialization error occurs\n96: WHEN initStore returns error\n97: THEN klog.Fatalf SHALL be called with message \"init store failed: %v\"\n98: ```\n99: \n100: ---\n101: \n102: ### REQ-004: Redis Client Initialization\n103: \n104: **GIVEN** Redis backend needs configuration  \n105: **WHEN** initializing Redis client  \n106: **THEN** environment variables shall be read correctly\n107: \n108: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n109: \n110: ```go\n111: // Scenario 1: Redis address required\n112: GIVEN REDIS_ADDR environment variable set to \"localhost:6379\"\n113: WHEN makeRedisOptions() is called\n114: THEN returned Options.Addr SHALL be \"localhost:6379\"\n115: \n116: // Scenario 2: Redis password passed\n117: GIVEN REDIS_PASSWORD environment variable set to \"secret\"\n118: WHEN makeRedisOptions() is called\n119: THEN returned Options.Password SHALL be \"secret\"\n120: \n121: // Scenario 3: Password required by default\n122: GIVEN REDIS_ADDR set and REDIS_PASSWORD empty and REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED unset\n123: WHEN Redis store initializes\n124: THEN initialization SHALL fail with password required error\n125: \n126: // Scenario 4: Password optional when disabled\n127: GIVEN REDIS_ADDR set and REDIS_PASSWORD empty and REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=\"false\"\n128: WHEN Redis store initializes\n129: THEN initialization SHALL succeed with empty password\n130: \n131: // Scenario 5: REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED case insensitive\n132: GIVEN REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=\"FALSE\"\n133: WHEN checking password requirement\n134: THEN comparison SHALL be case-insensitive\n135: ```\n136: \n137: ---\n138: \n139: ### REQ-005: Redis Store Struct\n140: \n141: **GIVEN** Redis implementation needs state  \n142: **WHEN** defining redisStore struct  \n143: **THEN** required fields shall be present\n144: \n145: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n146: \n147: ```go\n148: // Scenario 1: redisStore struct definition\n149: GIVEN pkg/store/store_redis.go\n150: WHEN reading the struct\n151: THEN redisStore SHALL contain cli *redisv9.Client\n152: AND redisStore SHALL contain sessionPrefix string\n153: AND redisStore SHALL contain expiryIndexKey string\n154: AND redisStore SHALL contain lastActivityIndexKey string\n155: \n156: // Scenario 2: sessionPrefix value\n157: GIVEN redisStore instance\n158: WHEN initialized\n159: THEN sessionPrefix SHALL be \"session:\"\n160: \n161: // Scenario 3: expiryIndexKey value\n162: GIVEN redisStore instance\n163: WHEN initialized\n164: THEN expiryIndexKey SHALL be \"session:expiry\"\n165: \n166: // Scenario 4: lastActivityIndexKey value\n167: GIVEN redisStore instance\n168: WHEN initialized\n169: THEN lastActivityIndexKey SHALL be \"session:last_activity\"\n170: ```\n171: \n172: ---\n173: \n174: ### REQ-006: Key Naming Convention\n175: \n176: **GIVEN** session data needs consistent key format  \n177: **WHEN** constructing Redis keys  \n178: **THEN** prefix pattern shall be used\n179: \n180: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n181: \n182: ```go\n183: // Scenario 1: sessionKey function\n184: GIVEN pkg/store/store_redis.go\n185: WHEN reading sessionKey function\n186: THEN it SHALL return sessionPrefix + sessionID\n187: \n188: // Scenario 2: Session key format\n189: GIVEN session ID \"abc123\"\n190: WHEN sessionKey(\"abc123\") is called\n191: THEN result SHALL be \"session:abc123\"\n192: ```\n193: \n194: ---\n195: \n196: ### REQ-007: Ping Connectivity\n197: \n198: **GIVEN** connectivity verification needed  \n199: **WHEN** calling Ping  \n200: **THEN** Redis PING command shall be issued\n201: \n202: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n203: \n204: ```go\n205: // Scenario 1: Ping returns nil on success\n206: GIVEN connected Redis client\n207: WHEN Ping(ctx) is called\n208: THEN Redis PING command SHALL be issued\n209: AND return SHALL be nil when response equals \"PONG\"\n210: \n211: // Scenario 2: Ping returns error on failure\n212: GIVEN unreachable Redis server\n213: WHEN Ping(ctx) is called\n214: THEN error from Redis client SHALL be returned\n215: ```\n216: \n217: ---\n218: \n219: ### REQ-008: Get Sandbox By Session ID\n220: \n221: **GIVEN** session lookup needed  \n222: **WHEN** calling GetSandboxBySessionID  \n223: **THEN** correct Redis GET shall be issued\n224: \n225: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n226: \n227: ```go\n228: // Scenario 1: Get existing session\n229: GIVEN key \"session:abc\" exists with valid JSON\n230: WHEN GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"abc\") is called\n231: THEN Redis GET session:abc SHALL be issued\n232: AND returned *types.SandboxInfo SHALL be unmarshaled from JSON\n233: \n234: // Scenario 2: Get missing session\n235: GIVEN no key \"session:xyz\"\n236: WHEN GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"xyz\") is called\n237: THEN redis.Nil error SHALL be detected\n238: AND method SHALL return nil, ErrNotFound\n239: \n240: // Scenario 3: JSON unmarshal error handled\n241: GIVEN key \"session:abc\" with invalid JSON\n242: WHEN GetSandboxBySessionID is called\n243: THEN unmarshal error SHALL be returned\n244: ```\n245: \n246: ---\n247: \n248: ### REQ-009: Store Sandbox Atomically\n249: \n250: **GIVEN** new session creation needed  \n251: **WHEN** calling StoreSandbox  \n252: **THEN** atomic pipeline shall execute\n253: \n254: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n255: \n256: ```go\n257: // Scenario 1: Reject nil sandbox\n258: GIVEN nil sandbox parameter\n259: WHEN StoreSandbox(ctx, nil) is called\n260: THEN error SHALL be returned indicating sandbox is nil\n261: \n262: // Scenario 2: Reject zero expiry\n263: GIVEN sandbox with ExpiresAt being zero time.Time{}\n264: WHEN StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox) is called\n265: THEN error SHALL be returned indicating invalid expiry\n266: \n267: // Scenario 3: Pipeline executes SETNX, ZADD expiry, ZADD activity\n268: GIVEN valid sandbox with SessionID \"s1\" and ExpiresAt t\n269: WHEN StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox) is called\n270: THEN pipeline SHALL execute SETNX session:s1 <json>\n271: AND pipeline SHALL execute ZADD session:expiry <t.Unix()> s1\n272: AND pipeline SHALL execute ZADD session:last_activity <now.Unix()> s1\n273: AND return SHALL be nil on success\n274: \n275: // Scenario 4: Reject duplicate session\n276: GIVEN key \"session:s1\" already exists\n277: WHEN StoreSandbox for same session ID is called\n278: THEN SETNX SHALL return false\n279: AND error SHALL indicate session already exists\n280: \n281: // Scenario 5: Pipeline failure returns error\n282: GIVEN any command in pipeline fails\n283: WHEN StoreSandbox processes pipeline\n284: THEN error SHALL be returned\n285: ```\n286: \n287: ---\n288: \n289: ### REQ-010: Update Sandbox\n290: \n291: **GIVEN** session data update needed  \n292: **WHEN** calling UpdateSandbox  \n293: **THEN** SET with XX shall be issued\n294: \n295: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n296: \n297: ```go\n298: // Scenario 1: Update existing session\n299: GIVEN key \"session:s1\" exists\n300: WHEN UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox) is called\n301: THEN Redis SET session:s1 <json> XX SHALL be issued\n302: AND return SHALL be nil on success\n303: \n304: // Scenario 2: Update missing session\n305: GIVEN key \"session:s1\" does not exist\n306: WHEN UpdateSandbox is called\n307: THEN SET with XX SHALL return false\n308: AND error SHALL indicate key does not exist\n309: \n310: // Scenario 3: Indexes not modified\n311: GIVEN UpdateSandbox called\n312: WHEN executing the method\n313: THEN expiry ZSET SHALL NOT be modified\n314: AND last_activity ZSET SHALL NOT be modified\n315: ```\n316: \n317: ---\n318: \n319: ### REQ-011: Delete Sandbox\n320: \n321: **GIVEN** session removal needed  \n322: **WHEN** calling DeleteSandboxBySessionID  \n323: **THEN** atomic cleanup shall execute\n324: \n325: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n326: \n327: ```go\n328: // Scenario 1: Delete existing session atomically\n329: GIVEN session \"s1\" exists with ZSET entries\n330: WHEN DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"s1\") is called\n331: THEN pipeline SHALL execute DEL session:s1\n332: AND pipeline SHALL execute ZREM session:expiry s1\n333: AND pipeline SHALL execute ZREM session:last_activity s1\n334: AND return SHALL be nil\n335: \n336: // Scenario 2: Delete missing session succeeds\n337: GIVEN session \"s1\" does not exist\n338: WHEN DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"s1\") is called\n339: THEN pipeline SHALL still execute DEL and ZREM\n340: AND return SHALL be nil (no error for missing)\n341: ```\n342: \n343: ---\n344: \n345: ### REQ-012: List Expired Sandboxes\n346: \n347: **GIVEN** expiry-based cleanup needed  \n348: **WHEN** calling ListExpiredSandboxes  \n349: **THEN** ZRANGEBYSCORE shall be used\n350: \n351: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n352: \n353: ```go\n354: // Scenario 1: Zero limit returns nil\n355: GIVEN limit <= 0\n356: WHEN ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit) is called\n357: THEN return SHALL be nil, nil without Redis calls\n358: \n359: // Scenario 2: ZRANGEBYSCORE with limit\n360: GIVEN ZSET session:expiry contains entries\n361: AND before = 2025-01-01T00:00:00Z\n362: AND limit = 10\n363: WHEN ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit) is called\n364: THEN ZRANGEBYSCORE session:expiry -inf <before.Unix()> LIMIT 0 10 SHALL be issued\n365: \n366: // Scenario 3: Pipeline GET for each session ID\n367: GIVEN ZRANGEBYSCORE returns session IDs\n368: WHEN loading sandbox data\n369: THEN pipeline GET session:{id} SHALL be issued for each ID\n370: AND slice of *types.SandboxInfo SHALL be returned\n371: \n372: // Scenario 4: Skip orphan ZSET entries\n373: GIVEN session ID \"orphan1\" in expiry ZSET but no session:orphan1 key\n374: WHEN loading sandbox data\n375: THEN orphan entry SHALL be skipped without error\n376: AND other valid sessions SHALL be returned\n377: ```\n378: \n379: ---\n380: \n381: ### REQ-013: List Inactive Sandboxes\n382: \n383: **GIVEN** activity-based cleanup needed  \n384: **WHEN** calling ListInactiveSandboxes  \n385: **THEN** activity index shall be queried\n386: \n387: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n388: \n389: ```go\n390: // Scenario 1: ZRANGEBYSCORE on activity index\n391: GIVEN ZSET session:last_activity contains entries\n392: AND before and limit are valid\n393: WHEN ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit) is called\n394: THEN ZRANGEBYSCORE session:last_activity -inf <before.Unix()> LIMIT 0 limit SHALL be issued\n395: \n396: // Scenario 2: Session data loaded via pipeline\n397: GIVEN ZRANGEBYSCORE returns session IDs\n398: WHEN processing results\n399: THEN session data SHALL be loaded via pipeline GETs\n400: ```\n401: \n402: ---\n403: \n404: ### REQ-014: Update Session Last Activity\n405: \n406: **GIVEN** activity timestamp update needed  \n407: **WHEN** calling UpdateSessionLastActivity  \n408: **THEN** existence check shall precede ZADD\n409: \n410: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n411: \n412: ```go\n413: // Scenario 1: Reject empty session ID\n414: GIVEN empty sessionID string\n415: WHEN UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"\", at) is called\n416: THEN error SHALL indicate session ID is empty\n417: \n418: // Scenario 2: Use current time when at is zero\n419: GIVEN key \"session:s1\" exists\n420: AND at is zero time.Time{}\n421: WHEN UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"s1\", at) is called\n422: THEN time.Now() SHALL be used for the score\n423: \n424: // Scenario 3: Update activity for existing session\n425: GIVEN key \"session:s1\" exists\n426: AND at is non-zero time\n427: WHEN UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"s1\", at) is called\n428: THEN ZADD session:last_activity <at.Unix()> s1 SHALL be issued\n429: AND return SHALL be nil\n430: \n431: // Scenario 4: Reject missing session\n432: GIVEN key \"session:s1\" does not exist\n433: WHEN UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"s1\", at) is called\n434: THEN ErrNotFound SHALL be returned\n435: ```\n436: \n437: ---\n438: \n439: ### REQ-015: Close Connection\n440: \n441: **GIVEN** graceful shutdown needed  \n442: **WHEN** calling Close  \n443: **THEN** Redis client shall be closed\n444: \n445: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n446: \n447: ```go\n448: // Scenario 1: Close succeeds\n449: GIVEN connected Redis client\n450: WHEN Close() is called\n451: THEN cli.Close() SHALL be invoked\n452: AND return SHALL be nil\n453: ```\n454: \n455: ---\n456: \n457: ### REQ-016: Store Type Selection\n458: \n459: **GIVEN** multiple backend options  \n460: **WHEN** initializing store  \n461: **THEN** correct backend shall be selected\n462: \n463: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n464: \n465: ```go\n466: // Scenario 1: Default to redis\n467: GIVEN STORE_TYPE not set\n468: WHEN initStore runs\n469: THEN Redis implementation SHALL be selected\n470: \n471: // Scenario 2: Explicit redis\n472: GIVEN STORE_TYPE = \"redis\"\n473: WHEN initStore runs\n474: THEN Redis implementation SHALL be selected\n475: \n476: // Scenario 3: Case-insensitive store type\n477: GIVEN STORE_TYPE = \"REDIS\"\n478: WHEN initStore runs\n479: THEN Redis implementation SHALL be selected\n480: \n481: // Scenario 4: Invalid store type\n482: GIVEN STORE_TYPE = \"unknown\"\n483: WHEN initStore runs\n484: THEN initialization SHALL fail with error\n485: ```\n486: \n487: ---\n488: \n489: ### REQ-017: SandboxInfo JSON Marshaling\n490: \n491: **GIVEN** sandbox data serialized as JSON  \n492: **WHEN** marshaling/unmarshaling  \n493: **THEN** correct field mapping shall be used\n494: \n495: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n496: \n497: ```go\n498: // Scenario 1: SandboxInfo JSON fields\n499: GIVEN types.SandboxInfo struct\n500: WHEN marshaled to JSON\n501: THEN Kind SHALL map to \"kind\"\n502: AND SandboxID SHALL map to \"sandboxId\"\n503: AND SandboxNamespace SHALL map to \"sandboxNamespace\"\n504: AND Name SHALL map to \"name\"\n505: AND EntryPoints SHALL map to \"entryPoints\"\n506: AND SessionID SHALL map to \"sessionId\"\n507: AND CreatedAt SHALL map to \"createdAt\"\n508: AND ExpiresAt SHALL map to \"expiresAt\"\n509: AND Status SHALL map to \"status\"\n510: \n511: // Scenario 2: SandboxEntryPoint JSON fields\n512: GIVEN types.SandboxEntryPoint struct\n513: WHEN marshaled to JSON\n514: THEN Path SHALL map to \"path\"\n515: AND Protocol SHALL map to \"protocol\"\n516: AND Endpoint SHALL map to \"endpoint\"\n517: ```\n518: \n519: ---\n520: \n521: ### REQ-018: Unit Tests\n522: \n523: **GIVEN** implementation needs test coverage  \n524: **WHEN** verifying functionality  \n525: **THEN** unit tests shall cover all core components\n526: \n527: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n528: \n529: ```go\n530: // Scenario 1: Store interface tests\n531: GIVEN pkg/store/store_test.go\n532: WHEN running tests\n533: THEN ErrNotFound tests SHALL verify error message\n534: AND interface compliance SHALL be tested\n535: \n536: // Scenario 2: Redis store tests\n537: GIVEN pkg/store/store_redis_test.go\n538: WHEN running tests\n539: THEN Ping tests SHALL verify connectivity\n540: AND GetSandboxBySessionID tests SHALL verify lookup and not found\n541: AND StoreSandbox tests SHALL verify atomic creation and validation\n542: AND UpdateSandbox tests SHALL verify update semantics\n543: AND DeleteSandboxBySessionID tests SHALL verify cleanup\n544: AND ListExpiredSandboxes tests SHALL verify expiry query\n545: AND ListInactiveSandboxes tests SHALL verify activity query\n546: AND UpdateSessionLastActivity tests SHALL verify activity update\n547: \n548: // Scenario 3: Singleton tests\n549: GIVEN pkg/store/singleton_test.go\n550: WHEN running tests\n551: THEN Storage() tests SHALL verify singleton behavior\n552: AND concurrent access SHALL be tested\n553: AND store type selection SHALL be tested\n554: ```\n555: \n556: ---\n557: \n558: ### REQ-019: Code Quality\n559: \n560: **GIVEN** code needs to meet quality standards  \n561: **WHEN** running linting and validation  \n562: **THEN** code shall pass go vet and build\n563: \n564: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n565: \n566: ```go\n567: // Scenario 1: go vet passes\n568: GIVEN pkg/store/\n569: WHEN running go vet ./pkg/store/...\n570: THEN zero issues SHALL be reported\n571: \n572: // Scenario 2: Build succeeds\n573: GIVEN pkg/store/\n574: WHEN running go build ./pkg/store/...\n575: THEN build SHALL succeed without errors\n576: \n577: // Scenario 3: All tests pass\n578: GIVEN pkg/store/\n579: WHEN running go test ./pkg/store/...\n580: THEN all tests SHALL pass without failures\n581: ```\n582: \n583: ---\n584: \n585: ## Implementation Files\n586: \n587: | File | Purpose |\n588: |------|---------|\n589: | `pkg/store/store.go` | Store interface and ErrNotFound error |\n590: | `pkg/store/store_redis.go` | Redis implementation with all methods |\n591: | `pkg/store/store_valkey.go` | Valkey implementation |\n592: | `pkg/store/singleton.go` | Storage() singleton access and initStore |\n593: | `pkg/store/store_test.go` | Interface tests |\n594: | `pkg/store/store_redis_test.go` | Redis implementation tests |\n595: | `pkg/store/singleton_test.go` | Singleton tests |\n596: | `pkg/common/types/sandbox.go` | SandboxInfo and SandboxEntryPoint types |\n597: \n598: ---\n599: \n600: ## Dependencies\n601: \n602: | Package | Purpose |\n603: |---------|---------|\n604: | `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` | Redis client library |\n605: | `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` | Valkey client library |\n606: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` | SandboxInfo types |\n607: | `k8s.io/klog/v2` | Logging |\n608: | `context` | Request context |\n609: | `time` | Timestamp handling |\n610: | `sync` | Singleton initialization |\n611: \n612: ---\n613: \n614: ## Redis Operations Summary\n615: \n616: | Method | Redis Commands |\n617: |--------|----------------|\n618: | `Ping` | `PING` â†’ expect `PONG` |\n619: | `GetSandboxBySessionID` | `GET session:{id}` |\n620: | `StoreSandbox` | Pipeline: `SETNX`, `ZADD session:expiry`, `ZADD session:last_activity` |\n621: | `UpdateSandbox` | `SET key value XX` |\n622: | `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` | Pipeline: `DEL`, `ZREM expiry`, `ZREM last_activity` |\n623: | `ListExpiredSandboxes` | `ZRANGEBYSCORE session:expiry -inf {before.Unix} LIMIT 0 limit` then pipeline GETs |\n624: | `ListInactiveSandboxes` | `ZRANGEBYSCORE session:last_activity ...` then pipeline GETs |\n625: | `UpdateSessionLastActivity` | `GET` (existence), then `ZADD session:last_activity` |\n626: | `Close` | `cli.Close()` |\n627: \n628: ---\n629: \n630: ## ZSET Score Semantics\n631: \n632: | Index Key | Score Value | Member |\n633: |-----------|-------------|--------|\n634: | `session:expiry` | `ExpiresAt.Unix()` | session ID |\n635: | `session:last_activity` | `time.Now().Unix()` on store, `at.Unix()` on update | session ID |\n636: \n637: ---\n638: \n639: ## Environment Variables\n640: \n641: | Variable | Required | Default | Notes |\n642: |----------|----------|---------|--------|\n643: | `REDIS_ADDR` | Yes | - | Redis server address |\n644: | `REDIS_PASSWORD` | Yes (unless disabled) | - | Case-insensitive check for \"false\" |\n645: | `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` | No | - | Set to \"false\" to disable password |\n646: | `STORE_TYPE` | No | `redis` | Case-insensitive |\n647: \n648: ---\n649: \n650: ## Validation Checklist\n651: \n652: - [ ] Store interface defined with all 9 methods\n653: - [ ] ErrNotFound exported with correct message\n654: - [ ] Redis store type constants defined\n655: - [ ] Singleton pattern correctly implemented\n656: - [ ] Redis client initialized from environment\n657: - [ ] Key naming uses \"session:\" prefix\n658: - [ ] Ping verifies connectivity\n659: - [ ] GetSandboxBySessionID handles found/not found\n660: - [ ] StoreSandbox validates input and uses atomic pipeline\n661: - [ ] UpdateSandbox uses SET XX semantics\n662: - [ ] DeleteSandboxBySessionID cleans all indexes\n663: - [ ] ListExpiredSandboxes queries expiry ZSET\n664: - [ ] ListInactiveSandboxes queries activity ZSET\n665: - [ ] UpdateSessionLastActivity checks existence\n666: - [ ] Close gracefully shuts down client\n667: - [ ] Store type selection works correctly\n668: - [ ] Pass `go vet` with zero issues\n669: - [ ] Build succeeds without errors\n670: - [ ] All tests pass\n\n(End of file - total 670 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-013: Redis Storage Implementation\n\nModule: `pkg/store`\nLanguage: Go\nSize: M\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nImplement Redis-backed session storage for persisting sandbox metadata keyed by session ID, with sorted set indexes for expiry and last-activity tracking.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### REQ-001: Store Interface\n\n**GIVEN** the system needs to persist sandbox metadata  \n**WHEN** managing session storage  ","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775858799600,"end":1775858799619}}}}
