{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775858803185,"sessionID":"ses_286938d3effeSPFC7LqkvWW4EL","part":{"id":"prt_d796ee1f0001liBY0LwfXXSVjn","messageID":"msg_d796ed43a001kDhaV61z0x37zt","sessionID":"ses_286938d3effeSPFC7LqkvWW4EL","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775858921685,"sessionID":"ses_286938d3effeSPFC7LqkvWW4EL","part":{"id":"prt_d7970b042001zvTT2552px0Bkp","messageID":"msg_d796ed43a001kDhaV61z0x37zt","sessionID":"ses_286938d3effeSPFC7LqkvWW4EL","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-feb25c24e8174f93afe0a3ead9238e1e","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-014: Valkey Storage Implementation\n\nModule: `pkg/store`\nLanguage: Go\nSize: S\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nImplement Valkey-backed session storage for persisting sandbox metadata keyed by session ID, with sorted set indexes for expiry and last-activity tracking. This delta implements `store_valkey.go` using `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` client.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### REQ-001: Valkey Client Initialization\n\n**GIVEN** Valkey backend needs configuration  \n**WHEN** initializing Valkey client  \n**THEN** environment variables shall be read correctly\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```go\n// Scenario 1: Valkey address required\nGIVEN VALKEY_ADDR environment variable set to \"localhost:6379\"\nWHEN makeValkeyOptions() is called\nTHEN returned ClientOption.InitAddress SHALL be [\"localhost:6379\"]\n\n// Scenario 2: Valkey address comma-separated\nGIVEN VALKEY_ADDR environment variable set to \"host1:6379,host2:6379\"\nWHEN makeValkeyOptions() is called\nTHEN returned ClientOption.InitAddress SHALL be [\"host1:6379\", \"host2:6379\"]\n\n// Scenario 3: Valkey password passed\nGIVEN VALKEY_PASSWORD environment variable set to \"secret\"\nWHEN makeValkeyOptions() is called\nTHEN returned ClientOption.Password SHALL be \"secret\"\n\n// Scenario 4: Password required by default\nGIVEN VALKEY_ADDR set and VALKEY_PASSWORD empty and VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED unset\nWHEN Valkey store initializes\nTHEN initialization SHALL fail with password required error\n\n// Scenario 5: Password optional when disabled\nGIVEN VALKEY_ADDR set and VALKEY_PASSWORD empty and VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=\"false\"\nWHEN Valkey store initializes\nTHEN initialization SHALL succeed with empty password\n\n// Scenario 6: VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED case insensitive\nGIVEN VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=\"FALSE\"\nWHEN checking password requirement\nTHEN comparison SHALL be case-insensitive\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-002: Valkey Optional Client Flags\n\n**GIVEN** optional Valkey client configuration  \n**WHEN** building client options  \n**THEN** optional flags shall be set correctly\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```go\n// Scenario 1: DisableCache enabled\nGIVEN VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE=\"true\"\nWHEN makeValkeyOptions() is called\nTHEN ClientOption.DisableCache SHALL be true\n\n// Scenario 2: DisableCache ignored when not true\nGIVEN VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE=\"yes\"\nWHEN makeValkeyOptions() is called\nTHEN ClientOption.DisableCache SHALL NOT be set\n\n// Scenario 3: ForceSingleClient enabled\nGIVEN VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE=\"true\"\nWHEN makeValkeyOptions() is called\nTHEN ClientOption.ForceSingleClient SHALL be true\n\n// Scenario 4: Both flags enabled\nGIVEN VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE=\"true\" and VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE=\"true\"\nWHEN makeValkeyOptions() is called\nTHEN ClientOption.DisableCache SHALL be true\nAND ClientOption.ForceSingleClient SHALL be true\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-003: Valkey Store Struct\n\n**GIVEN** Valkey implementation needs state  \n**WHEN** defining valkeyStore struct  \n**THEN** required fields shall be present\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```go\n// Scenario 1: valkeyStore struct definition\nGIVEN pkg/store/store_valkey.go\nWHEN reading the struct\nTHEN valkeyStore SHALL contain cli valkey.Client\nAND valkeyStore SHALL contain sessionPrefix string\nAND valkeyStore SHALL contain expiryIndexKey string\nAND valkeyStore SHALL contain lastActivityIndexKey string\n\n// Scenario 2: sessionPrefix value\nGIVEN valkeyStore instance\nWHEN initialized\nTHEN sessionPrefix SHALL be \"session:\"\n\n// Scenario 3: expiryIndexKey value\nGIVEN valkeyStore instance\nWHEN initialized\nTHEN expiryIndexKey SHALL be \"session:expiry\"\n\n// Scenario 4: lastActivityIndexKey value\nGIVEN valkeyStore instance\nWHEN initialized\nTHEN lastActivityIndexKey SHALL be \"session:last_activity\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-004: Valkey Ping Implementation\n\n**GIVEN** connectivity verification needed  \n**WHEN** calling Ping  \n**THEN** Valkey PING command shall be issued\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```go\n// Scenario 1: Ping returns nil on success\nGIVEN connected Valkey client\nWHEN Ping(ctx) is called\nTHEN command B().Ping().Build() SHALL be executed\nAND return SHALL be nil when response equals \"PONG\"\n\n// Scenario 2: Ping returns error on failure\nGIVEN unreachable Valkey server\nWHEN Ping(ctx) is called\nTHEN error from Valkey client SHALL be returned\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-005: Valkey GetSandboxBySessionID Implementation\n\n**GIVEN** session lookup needed  \n**WHEN** calling GetSandboxBySessionID  \n**THEN** correct Valkey GET shall be issued\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```go\n// Scenario 1: Get existing session\nGIVEN key \"session:abc\" exists with valid JSON\nWHEN GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"abc\") is called\nTHEN command B().Get().Key(\"session:abc\").Build() SHALL be executed\nAND returned *types.SandboxInfo SHALL be unmarshaled from response bytes\n\n// Scenario 2: Get missing session\nGIVEN no key \"session:xyz\"\nWHEN GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"xyz\") is called\nTHEN IsValkeyNil(response) SHALL be true\nAND method SHALL return nil, ErrNotFound\n\n// Scenario 3: JSON unmarshal error handled\nGIVEN key \"session:abc\" with invalid JSON\nWHEN GetSandboxBySessionID is called\nTHEN unmarshal error SHALL be returned\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-006: Valkey StoreSandbox Implementation\n\n**GIVEN** new session creation needed  \n**WHEN** calling StoreSandbox  \n**THEN** atomic DoMulti shall execute\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```go\n// Scenario 1: Reject nil sandbox\nGIVEN nil sandbox parameter\nWHEN StoreSandbox(ctx, nil) is called\nTHEN error SHALL be returned indicating sandbox is nil\n\n// Scenario 2: Reject zero expiry\nGIVEN sandbox with ExpiresAt being zero time.Time{}\nWHEN StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox) is called\nTHEN error SHALL be returned indicating invalid expiry\n\n// Scenario 3: DoMulti executes SETNX, ZADD expiry, ZADD activity\nGIVEN valid sandbox with SessionID \"s1\" and ExpiresAt t\nWHEN StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox) is called\nTHEN DoMulti SHALL execute SETNX session:s1 <json>\nAND DoMulti SHALL execute ZADD session:expiry <t.Unix()> s1\nAND DoMulti SHALL execute ZADD session:last_activity <now.Unix()> s1\nAND return SHALL be nil on success\n\n// Scenario 4: Reject duplicate session\nGIVEN key \"session:s1\" already exists\nWHEN StoreSandbox for same session ID is called\nTHEN SETNX SHALL return 0\nAND error SHALL indicate session already exists\n\n// Scenario 5: DoMulti failure returns error\nGIVEN any command in DoMulti fails\nWHEN StoreSandbox processes results\nTHEN error SHALL be returned\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-007: Valkey UpdateSandbox Implementation\n\n**GIVEN** session data update needed  \n**WHEN** calling UpdateSandbox  \n**THEN** SET with XX shall be issued\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```go\n// Scenario 1: Update existing session\nGIVEN key \"session:s1\" exists\nWHEN UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox) is called\nTHEN command SET session:s1 <json> XX SHALL be built\nAND response.ToString() SHALL equal \"OK\"\nAND return SHALL be nil on success\n\n// Scenario 2: Update missing session\nGIVEN key \"session:s1\" does not exist\nWHEN UpdateSandbox is called\nTHEN response.ToString() SHALL NOT equal \"OK\"\nAND error SHALL indicate key does not exist\n\n// Scenario 3: Indexes not modified\nGIVEN UpdateSandbox called\nWHEN executing the method\nTHEN expiry ZSET SHALL NOT be modified\nAND last_activity ZSET SHALL NOT be modified\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-008: Valkey DeleteSandboxBySessionID Implementation\n\n**GIVEN** session removal needed  \n**WHEN** calling DeleteSandboxBySessionID  \n**THEN** atomic DoMulti cleanup shall execute\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```go\n// Scenario 1: Delete existing session atomically\nGIVEN session \"s1\" exists with ZSET entries\nWHEN DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"s1\") is called\nTHEN DoMulti SHALL execute DEL session:s1\nAND DoMulti SHALL execute ZREM session:expiry s1\nAND DoMulti SHALL execute ZREM session:last_activity s1\nAND return SHALL be nil\n\n// Scenario 2: Delete missing session succeeds\nGIVEN session \"s1\" does not exist\nWHEN DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"s1\") is called\nTHEN DoMulti SHALL still execute DEL and ZREM\nAND return SHALL be nil (no error for missing)\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-009: Valkey ListExpiredSandboxes Implementation\n\n**GIVEN** expiry-based cleanup needed  \n**WHEN** calling ListExpiredSandboxes  \n**THEN** ZRANGEBYSCORE shall be used\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```go\n// Scenario 1: Zero limit returns nil\nGIVEN limit <= 0\nWHEN ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit) is called\nTHEN return SHALL be nil, nil without Valkey calls\n\n// Scenario 2: ZRANGEBYSCORE with limit\nGIVEN ZSET session:expiry contains entries\nAND before = 2025-01-01T00:00:00Z\nAND limit = 10\nWHEN ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit) is called\nTHEN command Zrangebyscore session:expiry Min(\"-inf\") Max(\"<before.Unix()>\") Limit(0, 10) SHALL be built\n\n// Scenario 3: MGET for session data\nGIVEN ZRANGEBYSCORE returns session IDs [\"s1\", \"s2\"]\nWHEN loading sandbox data via loadSandboxesBySessionIDs\nTHEN MGET session:s1 session:s2 SHALL be executed\nAND slice of *types.SandboxInfo SHALL be returned\n\n// Scenario 4: Skip orphan ZSET entries\nGIVEN session ID \"orphan1\" in expiry ZSET but no session:orphan1 key\nWHEN MGET returns empty string for orphan1\nTHEN that entry SHALL be skipped without error\nAND other valid sessions SHALL be returned\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-010: Valkey ListInactiveSandboxes Implementation\n\n**GIVEN** activity-based cleanup needed  \n**WHEN** calling ListInactiveSandboxes  \n**THEN** activity index shall be queried\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```go\n// Scenario 1: ZRANGEBYSCORE on activity index\nGIVEN ZSET session:last_activity contains entries\nAND before and limit are valid\nWHEN ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit) is called\nTHEN command Zrangebyscore session:last_activity Min(\"-inf\") Max(\"<before.Unix()>\") Limit(0, limit) SHALL be built\n\n// Scenario 2: Session data loaded via MGET\nGIVEN ZRANGEBYSCORE returns session IDs\nWHEN processing results via loadSandboxesBySessionIDs\nTHEN session data SHALL be loaded via single MGET command\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-011: Valkey UpdateSessionLastActivity Implementation\n\n**GIVEN** activity timestamp update needed  \n**WHEN** calling UpdateSessionLastActivity  \n**THEN** existence check shall precede ZADD\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```go\n// Scenario 1: Reject empty session ID\nGIVEN empty sessionID string\nWHEN UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"\", at) is called\nTHEN error SHALL indicate session ID is empty\n\n// Scenario 2: Use current time when at is zero\nGIVEN key \"session:s1\" exists\nAND at is zero time.Time{}\nWHEN UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"s1\", at) is called\nTHEN time.Now() SHALL be used for the score\n\n// Scenario 3: Update activity for existing session\nGIVEN key \"session:s1\" exists\nAND at is non-zero time\nWHEN UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"s1\", at) is called\nTHEN EXISTS session:s1 SHALL return int64 1\nAND Zadd session:last_activity Score(<at.Unix()>).Member(\"s1\") SHALL be executed\nAND return SHALL be nil\n\n// Scenario 4: Reject missing session\nGIVEN key \"session:s1\" does not exist\nWHEN UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"s1\", at) is called\nTHEN EXISTS SHALL return int64 0\nAND ErrNotFound SHALL be returned\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-012: Valkey Close Implementation\n\n**GIVEN** graceful shutdown needed  \n**WHEN** calling Close  \n**THEN** Valkey client shall be closed\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```go\n// Scenario 1: Close succeeds\nGIVEN connected Valkey client\nWHEN Close() is called\nTHEN cli.Close() SHALL be invoked\nAND return SHALL be nil\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-013: MGET Optimization Implementation\n\n**GIVEN** multiple sandbox documents need loading  \n**WHEN** calling loadSandboxesBySessionIDs  \n**THEN** single MGET shall be used\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```go\n// Scenario 1: Build keys from session IDs\nGIVEN session IDs [\"abc\", \"def\"]\nWHEN loadSandboxesBySessionIDs is called\nTHEN keys SHALL be [\"session:abc\", \"session:def\"]\n\n// Scenario 2: Single MGET command\nGIVEN keys list built\nWHEN executing load\nTHEN B().Mget().Key(keys...).Build() SHALL be executed\n\n// Scenario 3: Process MGET results\nGIVEN MGET returns [bytes1, emptyVal, bytes2]\nWHEN processing results\nTHEN bytes1 SHALL be unmarshaled to SandboxInfo\nAND emptyVal SHALL be skipped (IsValkeyNil or empty string)\nAND bytes2 SHALL be unmarshaled to SandboxInfo\nAND result SHALL have 2 entries\n\n// Scenario 4: Slot comment for deployment\nGIVEN loadSandboxesBySessionIDs implementation\nWHEN reading the code\nTHEN comment SHALL indicate keys should be in same slot for cluster deployment\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-014: Valkey Store Type Selection\n\n**GIVEN** multiple backend options  \n**WHEN** initializing store with valkey  \n**THEN** Valkey backend shall be selected\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```go\n// Scenario 1: Valkey store type\nGIVEN STORE_TYPE = \"valkey\"\nWHEN initStore runs\nTHEN Valkey implementation SHALL be selected\n\n// Scenario 2: Case-insensitive valkey\nGIVEN STORE_TYPE = \"VALKEY\"\nWHEN initStore runs\nTHEN Valkey implementation SHALL be selected\n\n// Scenario 3: Valkey requires VALKEY_ADDR\nGIVEN STORE_TYPE = \"valkey\"\nAND VALKEY_ADDR not set\nWHEN initStore runs\nTHEN initialization SHALL fail with error indicating VALKEY_ADDR required\n\n// Scenario 4: Invalid store type still fails\nGIVEN STORE_TYPE = \"unknown\"\nWHEN initStore runs\nTHEN initialization SHALL fail with unsupported store type error\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-015: Valkey Command Builder Usage\n\n**GIVEN** Valkey client uses command builder pattern  \n**WHEN** executing operations  \n**THEN** correct builder chain shall be used\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```go\n// Scenario 1: Ping builder\nGIVEN Ping method\nWHEN building command\nTHEN B().Ping().Build() SHALL be used\n\n// Scenario 2: Get builder\nGIVEN GetSandboxBySessionID method\nWHEN building command\nTHEN B().Get().Key(key).Build() SHALL be used\n\n// Scenario 3: Set builder with NX\nGIVEN StoreSandbox SETNX\nWHEN building command\nTHEN B().Set().Key(key).Value(value).Nx().Build() SHALL be used\n\n// Scenario 4: Set builder with XX\nGIVEN UpdateSandbox\nWHEN building command\nTHEN B().Set().Key(key).Value(value).Xx().Build() SHALL be used\n\n// Scenario 5: ZADD builder\nGIVEN ZADD operations\nWHEN building command\nTHEN B().Zadd().Key(key).Score(score).Member(member).Build() SHALL be used\n\n// Scenario 6: ZRANGEBYSCORE builder\nGIVEN ZRANGEBYSCORE operations\nWHEN building command\nTHEN B().Zrangebyscore().Key(key).Min(min).Max(max).Limit(offset, count).Build() SHALL be used\n\n// Scenario 7: DEL builder\nGIVEN DEL operations\nWHEN building command\nTHEN B().Del().Key(key).Build() SHALL be used\n\n// Scenario 8: ZREM builder\nGIVEN ZREM operations\nWHEN building command\nTHEN B().Zrem().Key(key).Member(member).Build() SHALL be used\n\n// Scenario 9: EXISTS builder\nGIVEN EXISTS operations\nWHEN building command\nTHEN B().Exists().Key(key).Build() SHALL be used\n\n// Scenario 10: MGET builder\nGIVEN MGET operations\nWHEN building command\nTHEN B().Mget().Key(keys...).Build() SHALL be used\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-016: ZSET Score Semantics\n\n**GIVEN** sorted set indexes need numeric scores  \n**WHEN** adding to ZSET  \n**THEN** Unix timestamps shall be used as scores\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```go\n// Scenario 1: Expiry score on store\nGIVEN sandbox with ExpiresAt timestamp\nWHEN StoreSandbox adds to expiry ZSET\nTHEN score SHALL be float64(sandbox.ExpiresAt.Unix())\n\n// Scenario 2: Last activity score on store\nGIVEN StoreSandbox called\nWHEN adding to last_activity ZSET\nTHEN score SHALL be float64(time.Now().Unix())\n\n// Scenario 3: Last activity score on update\nGIVEN UpdateSessionLastActivity called with time at\nWHEN adding to last_activity ZSET\nTHEN score SHALL be float64(at.Unix())\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-017: Valkey Response Handling\n\n**GIVEN** Valkey client returns typed responses  \n**WHEN** processing response  \n**THEN** correct type extraction shall be used\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```go\n// Scenario 1: IsValkeyNil check\nGIVEN Valkey response\nWHEN checking for nil/missing\nTHEN resp.IsValkeyNil() SHALL be used for nil detection\n\n// Scenario 2: ToString for OK check\nGIVEN SET XX response\nWHEN checking success\nTHEN resp.ToString() SHALL equal \"OK\" for success\n\n// Scenario 3: AsBytes for data\nGIVEN GET response\nWHEN extracting data\nTHEN resp.AsBytes() SHALL return []byte for JSON unmarshal\n\n// Scenario 4: AsInt64 for EXISTS\nGIVEN EXISTS response\nWHEN checking existence\nTHEN resp.AsInt64() SHALL return 1 for exists, 0 for missing\n\n// Scenario 5: AsStringSlice for ZRANGEBYSCORE\nGIVEN ZRANGEBYSCORE response\nWHEN extracting member list\nTHEN resp.AsStringSlice() SHALL return session ID strings\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-018: Valkey DoMulti for Atomic Operations\n\n**GIVEN** multiple commands need atomic execution  \n**WHEN** executing pipelines  \n**THEN** DoMulti shall be used\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```go\n// Scenario 1: StoreSandbox uses DoMulti\nGIVEN StoreSandbox method\nWHEN executing atomic store\nTHEN DoMulti SHALL be used with SETNX, ZADD expiry, ZADD activity commands\n\n// Scenario 2: DeleteSandboxBySessionID uses DoMulti\nGIVEN DeleteSandboxBySessionID method\nWHEN executing atomic delete\nTHEN DoMulti SHALL be used with DEL, ZREM expiry, ZREM activity commands\n\n// Scenario 3: DoMulti returns slice of responses\nGIVEN DoMulti executed with N commands\nWHEN processing results\nTHEN responses SHALL be slice of valkey.ValkeyResult with length N\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-019: Unit Tests for Valkey Implementation\n\n**GIVEN** Valkey implementation needs test coverage  \n**WHEN** verifying functionality  \n**THEN** unit tests shall cover all methods\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```go\n// Scenario 1: Valkey store tests exist\nGIVEN pkg/store/store_valkey_test.go\nWHEN running tests\nTHEN Ping tests SHALL verify connectivity\nAND GetSandboxBySessionID tests SHALL verify lookup and not found\nAND StoreSandbox tests SHALL verify atomic creation and validation\nAND UpdateSandbox tests SHALL verify update semantics\nAND DeleteSandboxBySessionID tests SHALL verify cleanup\nAND ListExpiredSandboxes tests SHALL verify expiry query\nAND ListInactiveSandboxes tests SHALL verify activity query\nAND UpdateSessionLastActivity tests SHALL verify activity update\n\n// Scenario 2: Mock/miniredis used for tests\nGIVEN Valkey tests\nWHEN running tests\nTHEN mock Valkey server or miniredis SHALL be used for test isolation\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-020: Code Quality for Valkey\n\n**GIVEN** Valkey code needs to meet quality standards  \n**WHEN** running linting and validation  \n**THEN** code shall pass go vet and build\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```go\n// Scenario 1: go vet passes\nGIVEN pkg/store/store_valkey.go\nWHEN running go vet ./pkg/store/...\nTHEN zero issues SHALL be reported\n\n// Scenario 2: Build succeeds\nGIVEN pkg/store/store_valkey.go\nWHEN running go build ./pkg/store/...\nTHEN build SHALL succeed without errors\n\n// Scenario 3: All tests pass\nGIVEN pkg/store/\nWHEN running go test ./pkg/store/...\nTHEN all tests SHALL pass without failures\n```\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `pkg/store/store_valkey.go` | Valkey implementation with all methods |\n| `pkg/store/store_valkey_test.go` | Valkey implementation tests |\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Package | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|\n| `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` | Valkey client library |\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` | SandboxInfo types |\n| `k8s.io/klog/v2` | Logging (optional client flags) |\n| `context` | Request context |\n| `time` | Timestamp handling |\n| `strings` | Address splitting |\n| `strconv` | Bool parsing |\n| `os` | Environment variables |\n\n---\n\n## Valkey Operations Summary\n\n| Method | Valkey API / Builder |\n|--------|----------------------|\n| `Ping` | `B().Ping()` â†’ string `PONG` |\n| `GetSandboxBySessionID` | `B().Get().Key(key)` â†’ bytes; `IsValkeyNil` â†’ `ErrNotFound` |\n| `StoreSandbox` | `DoMulti`: `SETNX`, `ZADD` expiry, `ZADD` last_activity |\n| `UpdateSandbox` | `SET ... XX`; success requires `ToString() == \"OK\"` |\n| `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` | `DoMulti`: `DEL`, `ZREM` expiry, `ZREM` last_activity |\n| `ListExpiredSandboxes` | `Zrangebyscore` with `Min(\"-inf\")`, `Max(fmt.Sprintf(\"%d\", before.Unix()))`, `Limit(0, limit)` |\n| `ListInactiveSandboxes` | Same on `last_activity` key |\n| `UpdateSessionLastActivity` | `Exists` key â†’ int64 must be 1; then `Zadd` |\n| `Close` | `cli.Close()` |\n\n---\n\n## ZSET Score Semantics\n\n| Index Key | Score Value | Member |\n|-----------|-------------|--------|\n| `session:expiry` | `ExpiresAt.Unix()` | session ID |\n| `session:last_activity` | `time.Now().Unix()` on store, `at.Unix()` on update | session ID |\n\n---\n\n## Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Required | Default | Notes |\n|----------|----------|---------|--------|\n| `VALKEY_ADDR` | Yes | - | Comma-separated addresses |\n| `VALKEY_PASSWORD` | Yes (unless disabled) | - | Case-insensitive check for \"false\" |\n| `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` | No | - | Set to \"false\" to disable password |\n| `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` | No | - | ParseBool, must be true to enable |\n| `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` | No | - | ParseBool, must be true to enable |\n| `STORE_TYPE` | Must be `valkey` | `redis` | Case-insensitive |\n\n---\n\n## Validation Checklist\n\n- [ ] Valkey client initialized from environment with address splitting\n- [ ] Optional client flags (DisableCache, ForceSingleClient) supported\n- [ ] Password requirement configurable\n- [ ] valkeyStore struct with correct fields\n- [ ] Key naming uses \"session:\" prefix (same as Redis)\n- [ ] Ping verifies connectivity via B().Ping()\n- [ ] GetSandboxBySessionID handles found/not found via IsValkeyNil\n- [ ] StoreSandbox validates input and uses DoMulti for atomicity\n- [ ] UpdateSandbox uses SET XX and checks ToString() == \"OK\"\n- [ ] DeleteSandboxBySessionID uses DoMulti for cleanup\n- [ ] ListExpiredSandboxes uses Zrangebyscore builder\n- [ ] ListInactiveSandboxes uses Zrangebyscore builder\n- [ ] loadSandboxesBySessionIDs uses MGET for efficiency\n- [ ] UpdateSessionLastActivity checks EXISTS before Zadd\n- [ ] Close gracefully shuts down client\n- [ ] Store type selection supports \"valkey\" case-insensitively\n- [ ] Pass `go vet` with zero issues\n- [ ] Build succeeds without errors\n- [ ] All tests pass","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775858921583,"end":1775858921682}}}}
